'''''The Black Sands of Socorro''''' is a supplement to ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'' published by [[West End Games]]. It was written by [[Patricia A. Jackson]] and was first published in [[1997]].

The book was written from an [[in-universe]] perspective, and provided information on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] planet [[Socorro/Legends|Socorro]] and the rest of the [[Socorro system/Legends|Socorro system]]. The author attempts to create an Arabian-like ambience for the locations and characters encountered on the planet.

==Publisher's summary==
''A frontier world far from the tyranny of the Empire, Socorro offers opportunity, wealth&mdash;and danger!''

''Travel the Doaba Badlands, learn the secrets of the infamous Black Bha'lir smuggling coalition... explore a world as distinctive as its unforgettable ebony surface.''

==Contents==
*Prologue
*Chapter One: Socorro
*Chapter Two: Symbiotic Economics
*Chapter Three: [[Soco-Jarel Spaceport]]
*Chapter Four: [[Vakeyya]]: A City on the Edge
*Chapter Five: The Wilderness
*Chapter Six: [[Black Bha'lir|The Black Bha'lir]]
*Chapter Seven: [[Cjaalysce'I]]
*Chapter Eight: [[Abdi-Badawzi]], Monarch of the Sands
*Chapter Nine: Security Addendum: [[Saadoon-Kauldi's criminal empire]]
*Chapter Ten: [[Neftali/Legends|Neftali]]
*Scout's Addendum: [[Swoop/Legends|Swoopchasing!]]
*Story Starters
*Epilogue

